Combine spices and sugar; set aside. Cut circle in top of bread and remove bread center to make room for the Brie. Spread butter in bread; sprinkle with 2 teaspoons of spice mixture. With knife, make 2-inch cuts around edge of bread at 1-inch intervals. Remove rind from Brie and place in bread. Sprinkle Brie with remaining spice. Replace top of bread. Bake on baking sheet in 350 degrees F oven 20-30 minutes. To serve, remove bread top and break into bite size pieces. Dip bread pieces in hot Brie.